=You Are My Lover Friend=

26
00:01:35,580 --> 00:01:39,140
=Episode 13=
=Reunion Is Only Complete With You=

27
00:01:42,930 --> 00:01:44,360
We've reviewed the proposals

28
00:01:44,360 --> 00:01:45,300
from Jiujiang and CBBC.

29
00:01:45,690 --> 00:01:47,350
Do you have any additional comments?

30
00:01:57,130 --> 00:01:58,210
Nangang's aviation loan

31
00:01:58,210 --> 00:01:59,570
is a new project

32
00:01:59,570 --> 00:02:01,100
for us.

33
00:02:01,440 --> 00:02:02,720
We can bypass the credit check,

34
00:02:02,720 --> 00:02:03,560
audit it internally,

35
00:02:04,240 --> 00:02:05,090
and offer a loan

36
00:02:05,090 --> 00:02:06,010
3 to 5 times more

37
00:02:06,010 --> 00:02:07,350
than CBBC's under the same

38
00:02:07,850 --> 00:02:09,150
application conditions.

39
00:02:14,440 --> 00:02:16,530
Jiujiang does have some autonomy

40
00:02:16,530 --> 00:02:18,230
in loan amounts and approvals.

41
00:02:18,970 --> 00:02:20,200
But the minimum period

42
00:02:20,200 --> 00:02:22,020
for the aviation loan is five years.

43
00:02:22,410 --> 00:02:24,050
A low bad debt rate and stability

44
00:02:24,050 --> 00:02:24,950
are more important.

45
00:02:25,570 --> 00:02:26,810
In these two aspects,

46
00:02:26,810 --> 00:02:28,430
CBBC has unmatched advantages.

47
00:02:36,010 --> 00:02:37,670
Thank you, Mr. Zhou, Ms. Tang.

48
00:02:38,090 --> 00:02:39,430
We'll discuss it and tell you

49
00:02:39,640 --> 00:02:40,480
the results.

50
00:02:41,320 --> 00:02:42,160
Let's end

51
00:02:42,410 --> 00:02:43,250
the meeting here.

52
00:02:43,480 --> 00:02:44,320
Alright.

53
00:02:46,760 --> 00:02:48,580
- Ms. Tang and I
- Okay.

54
00:02:48,720 --> 00:02:50,180
seem to be fated.

55
00:02:50,920 --> 00:02:52,020
I don't believe in fate.

56
00:02:53,160 --> 00:02:54,900
Do you only believe in reason,

57
00:02:55,130 --> 00:02:55,970
not emotion?

58
00:02:56,480 --> 00:02:57,830
Emotion depends on the person.

59
00:02:59,570 --> 00:03:00,740
With some people,

60
00:03:01,440 --> 00:03:02,340
it's unnecessary.

61
00:03:04,600 --> 00:03:05,440
Let's stay in touch.

62
00:03:05,850 --> 00:03:07,180
- Stay in touch.
- Thank you.

63
00:03:14,690 --> 00:03:15,900
- Stay in touch.
- Sure.

64
00:03:17,010 --> 00:03:17,900
Alright, it's on.

65
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:21,110
- All set.
- Jiang is really something.

66
00:03:21,440 --> 00:03:23,130
Tang changed it himself.

67
00:03:23,130 --> 00:03:24,200
Didn't turn off the valve,

68
00:03:24,200 --> 00:03:25,740
and water sprayed all over the kitchen.

69
00:03:26,010 --> 00:03:26,970
I had to clean it up

70
00:03:26,970 --> 00:03:28,020
for ages.

71
00:03:29,320 --> 00:03:30,160
Actually,

72
00:03:30,290 --> 00:03:31,450
changing the water filter

73
00:03:31,450 --> 00:03:32,290
is very simple.

74
00:03:33,570 --> 00:03:35,150
But it needs to be done every 6 months.

75
00:03:35,480 --> 00:03:36,810
No worries. I've already set

76
00:03:36,810 --> 00:03:37,650
a reminder.

77
00:03:37,760 --> 00:03:38,600
Thank you, Uncle.

78
00:03:38,970 --> 00:03:39,920
Next time it needs it,

79
00:03:39,920 --> 00:03:40,830
I'll come over again.

80
00:03:41,040 --> 00:03:41,880
It's no trouble.

81
00:03:42,640 --> 00:03:43,480
Come on.

82
00:03:43,530 --> 00:03:44,550
- Sit.
- Have some fruit.

83
00:03:45,480 --> 00:03:46,340
Thank you, Ms. Zhou.

84
00:03:48,320 --> 00:03:49,180
Ms. Zhou.

85
00:03:49,440 --> 00:03:50,280
Dad.

86
00:03:52,850 --> 00:03:53,690
Am I lost?

87
00:03:53,700 --> 00:03:54,830
This is my home, right?

88
00:03:55,600 --> 00:03:56,440
We have a guest over.

89
00:03:56,440 --> 00:03:57,400
Come on. Sit, sit.

90
00:03:57,600 --> 00:03:58,690
Why are you here?

91
00:03:58,690 --> 00:03:59,720
Why can't I come?

92
00:03:59,720 --> 00:04:00,560
What's going on?

93
00:04:00,570 --> 00:04:01,640
Why did you tell us?

94
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:02,900
We've already finished dinner.

95
00:04:03,290 --> 00:04:05,340
I had a meeting nearby.

96
00:04:05,480 --> 00:04:07,200
I thought since it was close to home,

97
00:04:07,200 --> 00:04:08,300
I'd come over for a bite.

98
00:04:08,440 --> 00:04:09,730
Since you three

99
00:04:09,730 --> 00:04:10,760
have finished eating,

100
00:04:10,760 --> 00:04:11,600
I guess I can leave.

101
00:04:11,600 --> 00:04:12,510
Alright, alright.

102
00:04:12,640 --> 00:04:13,480
Okay, okay.

103
00:04:13,760 --> 00:04:14,600
Have some fruit.

104
00:04:14,610 --> 00:04:16,460
There's soup. I'll heat it up for you.

105
00:04:16,880 --> 00:04:17,950
- Come on.
- Let me help.

106
00:04:18,080 --> 00:04:19,160
- Sit down.
- Sit down.

107
00:04:19,170 --> 00:04:20,010
Alright, alright.

108
00:04:24,170 --> 00:04:25,010
Sit, sit, sit.

109
00:04:25,610 --> 00:04:26,660
Why is he here?

110
00:04:27,440 --> 00:04:29,660
He came to fix our water filter.

111
00:04:31,840 --> 00:04:32,900
Thank you, Master Jiang.

112
00:04:34,050 --> 00:04:35,150
Here, have some fruit.

113
00:04:35,370 --> 00:04:36,270
Pay me fifty.

114
00:04:38,640 --> 00:04:39,480
Come on.

115
00:04:40,400 --> 00:04:41,340
Have some more corn.

116
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:44,420
Work has drained my soul.

117
00:04:44,690 --> 00:04:45,760
One sip of this hot soup,

118
00:04:45,760 --> 00:04:46,980
and I feel revived.

119
00:04:47,690 --> 00:04:48,980
Don't just drink the soup.

120
00:04:49,250 --> 00:04:50,580
You need to eat some dishes too.

121
00:04:50,730 --> 00:04:52,020
Take your time. Don't choke.

122
00:04:52,250 --> 00:04:53,090
Come on.

123
00:04:53,250 --> 00:04:54,100
Sit down.

124
00:04:56,130 --> 00:04:56,970
Ms. Zhou,

125
00:04:57,730 --> 00:04:59,130
how are we spending

126
00:04:59,130 --> 00:05:00,190
the New Year this year?

127
00:05:00,370 --> 00:05:01,250
How?

128
00:05:01,250 --> 00:05:02,810
The same as always.

129
00:05:02,810 --> 00:05:04,310
We'll do it with her aunt's family.

130
00:05:05,130 --> 00:05:07,510
I've heard

131
00:05:08,050 --> 00:05:10,170
that New Year vacation trips

132
00:05:10,170 --> 00:05:11,220
are quite trendy lately.

133
00:05:11,730 --> 00:05:12,660
It's

134
00:05:12,930 --> 00:05:13,900
a few families together

135
00:05:14,370 --> 00:05:16,070
going to a tropical

136
00:05:16,250 --> 00:05:17,570
beach island.

137
00:05:17,570 --> 00:05:18,410
The weather

138
00:05:18,520 --> 00:05:19,610
will be cozy.

139
00:05:19,610 --> 00:05:22,050
Right. I have a colleague named Qin Yue.

140
00:05:22,050 --> 00:05:23,170
She took a few families

141
00:05:23,170 --> 00:05:24,810
to Sanya for a holiday.

142
00:05:24,810 --> 00:05:26,880
Yes, we could go together,
just the two families.

143
00:05:26,880 --> 00:05:28,050
We could hire a tour guide.

144
00:05:28,050 --> 00:05:28,890
Right?

145
00:05:29,170 --> 00:05:30,080
Can I spend

146
00:05:30,080 --> 00:05:31,050
the whole holiday

147
00:05:31,050 --> 00:05:31,960
sleeping in the hotel?

148
00:05:31,960 --> 00:05:32,800
Of course.

149
00:05:33,760 --> 00:05:35,340
We're okay with that,

150
00:05:35,490 --> 00:05:36,570
but her aunt can't fly.

151
00:05:36,570 --> 00:05:37,710
She's never taken a plane.

152
00:05:37,960 --> 00:05:39,730
It's the New Year, we can't just

153
00:05:39,730 --> 00:05:40,870
leave her behind, can we?

154
00:05:41,730 --> 00:05:44,420
If she doesn't want to fly,

155
00:05:44,760 --> 00:05:45,830
what about a cruise?

156
00:05:46,760 --> 00:05:48,250
Cruises seem pretty nice, too.

157
00:05:48,250 --> 00:05:49,170
On the cruise,

158
00:05:49,170 --> 00:05:50,010
no need to move.

159
00:05:50,050 --> 00:05:51,900
Just enjoy good food, beautiful views,

160
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:52,850
and evening shows.

161
00:05:52,850 --> 00:05:53,970
I heard the shows are great.

162
00:05:53,970 --> 00:05:55,880
Well, I've seen it in movies many times.

163
00:05:55,880 --> 00:05:56,760
It's really nice.

164
00:05:56,760 --> 00:05:57,850
So can we have barbeque

165
00:05:57,850 --> 00:05:58,690
on the deck

166
00:05:58,690 --> 00:05:59,970
while enjoying the sea breeze?

167
00:05:59,970 --> 00:06:00,810
Of course.

168
00:06:01,130 --> 00:06:02,440
Jiang, don't mention it.

169
00:06:02,440 --> 00:06:03,810
You forgot that year?

170
00:06:03,810 --> 00:06:05,520
Your mom and I tried something new

171
00:06:05,520 --> 00:06:07,050
and joined a cruise tour.

172
00:06:07,050 --> 00:06:07,890
In the end,

173
00:06:08,280 --> 00:06:10,400
both of us got vertigo.

174
00:06:10,400 --> 00:06:11,960
We felt dizzy all the time,

175
00:06:11,960 --> 00:06:13,420
lying in the cabin, vomiting,

176
00:06:13,730 --> 00:06:14,690
and couldn't go out.

177
00:06:14,690 --> 00:06:15,780
No, we can't do it.

178
00:06:16,170 --> 00:06:17,010
Right.

179
00:06:19,170 --> 00:06:21,020
Then I'll think about it.

180
00:06:23,570 --> 00:06:24,840
Why did you suddenly decide

181
00:06:24,840 --> 00:06:25,830
to come over today?

182
00:06:26,570 --> 00:06:27,870
I came to fix the water filter.

183
00:06:28,200 --> 00:06:29,310
Seriously?

184
00:06:31,370 --> 00:06:32,270
Yixiu is going

185
00:06:32,760 --> 00:06:35,580
to promote the co-branded sauce

186
00:06:35,730 --> 00:06:37,390
with Zhilan Snacks.

187
00:06:38,050 --> 00:06:40,390
The first batch of taste tests is out,

188
00:06:40,610 --> 00:06:41,650
so I thought I'd bring

189
00:06:41,650 --> 00:06:42,830
two boxes for Ms. Zhou to try

190
00:06:43,250 --> 00:06:44,420
to get some feedback.

191
00:06:45,320 --> 00:06:46,520
Who would've thought

192
00:06:46,520 --> 00:06:48,390
Zhilan Snacks would grow like this?

193
00:06:48,930 --> 00:06:50,640
I went there the other day.

194
00:06:50,640 --> 00:06:51,880
It was packed with customers.

195
00:06:51,880 --> 00:06:53,190
No time to clean the tables.

196
00:06:53,570 --> 00:06:54,950
It's all thanks to you

197
00:06:55,170 --> 00:06:56,870
for granting her the loan

198
00:06:57,280 --> 00:06:58,630
that helped her get started.

199
00:06:59,930 --> 00:07:01,200
It's also because

200
00:07:01,200 --> 00:07:03,200
of your short promotional video.

201
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:04,050
It made Zhilan Snacks

202
00:07:04,050 --> 00:07:05,420
an instant internet hit.

203
00:07:07,880 --> 00:07:09,150
So, in a way,

204
00:07:10,170 --> 00:07:11,830
Zhilan Snacks is a project

205
00:07:13,320 --> 00:07:14,510
we both contributed to.

206
00:07:15,080 --> 00:07:16,420
You're really thick-skinned.

207
00:07:16,690 --> 00:07:18,200
Zhilan didn't even say anything.

208
00:07:18,200 --> 00:07:19,830
Why is it our project now?

209
00:07:20,170 --> 00:07:21,010
Let me tell you.

210
00:07:21,320 --> 00:07:22,320
We formed a joint venture

211
00:07:22,320 --> 00:07:23,540
with Zhang Zhilan.

212
00:07:23,880 --> 00:07:25,730
We're going to expand Zhilan Snacks.

213
00:07:25,730 --> 00:07:27,020
I've ordered the production line.

214
00:07:28,640 --> 00:07:29,480
Now,

215
00:07:30,050 --> 00:07:31,070
it's really ours, right?

216
00:07:33,640 --> 00:07:34,840
It's still Yixiu's.

217
00:07:34,840 --> 00:07:36,220
What does it have to do with me?

218
00:07:38,840 --> 00:07:39,680
By the way,

219
00:07:40,320 --> 00:07:41,920
from what you just said,

220
00:07:41,920 --> 00:07:43,440
you want to travel for the New Year?

221
00:07:43,440 --> 00:07:44,830
Not going to your grandfather's?

222
00:07:47,760 --> 00:07:48,710
Why are you smiling?

223
00:07:49,370 --> 00:07:51,010
It's nothing. Go on upstairs.

224
00:07:51,010 --> 00:07:51,850
It's cold outside.

225
00:07:52,250 --> 00:07:54,100
I ate too much just now.

226
00:07:54,440 --> 00:07:56,440
Now my stomach feels
a little uncomfortable.

227
00:07:56,440 --> 00:07:58,150
I want to take a walk to digest.

228
00:07:59,640 --> 00:08:00,960
I thought you came to see me off.

229
00:08:00,960 --> 00:08:01,800
As it turns out,

230
00:08:02,170 --> 00:08:03,660
you dragged me down for your walk.

231
00:08:04,010 --> 00:08:04,870
No difference.

232
00:08:05,840 --> 00:08:06,680
True.

233
00:08:10,050 --> 00:08:11,580
In view of Zhang Zhilan's case,

234
00:08:11,760 --> 00:08:13,270
which balances

235
00:08:13,400 --> 00:08:14,420
compliance requirements,

236
00:08:14,810 --> 00:08:16,050
humanitarian care,

237
00:08:16,050 --> 00:08:17,150
and positive public opinion,

238
00:08:17,400 --> 00:08:19,900
we hereby award Tang Yang
from the Credit Audit Division

239
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:21,630
a commendation from the head office.

240
00:08:30,250 --> 00:08:31,090
Congratulations.

241
00:08:32,130 --> 00:08:33,130
I just lost

242
00:08:33,130 --> 00:08:34,350
an aviation loan case.

243
00:08:34,640 --> 00:08:35,920
I'm unworthy

244
00:08:35,920 --> 00:08:36,990
of this commendation.

245
00:08:37,850 --> 00:08:39,020
Each case is separate.

246
00:08:39,520 --> 00:08:40,630
I reviewed that case.

247
00:08:41,040 --> 00:08:42,450
We couldn't give them what Jiujiang

248
00:08:42,450 --> 00:08:43,300
was offering.

249
00:08:44,010 --> 00:08:45,020
Even if we secured it,

250
00:08:45,250 --> 00:08:46,420
it might not have been good.

251
00:08:47,490 --> 00:08:48,330
Come on.

252
00:08:51,940 --> 00:08:53,220
(Happy New Year)

253
00:08:53,250 --> 00:08:54,250
Thank you, Mr. Zhou,

254
00:08:54,250 --> 00:08:55,820
for your guidance and encouragement.

255
00:08:56,280 --> 00:08:58,110
Continue to work hard.

256
00:08:59,210 --> 00:09:00,270
Well done, Tang Yang.

257
00:09:00,560 --> 00:09:01,420
Thank you, Mr. Zhou.

258
00:09:03,680 --> 00:09:04,560
She lost the case

259
00:09:04,560 --> 00:09:05,680
but still got a commendation?

260
00:09:05,680 --> 00:09:06,730
Director Tang must have

261
00:09:06,730 --> 00:09:07,570
strong connections.

262
00:09:07,580 --> 00:09:08,440
That's right.

263
00:09:08,450 --> 00:09:09,800
Anyone else would've been

264
00:09:09,800 --> 00:09:10,780
harshly criticized.

265
00:09:11,010 --> 00:09:12,010
Ms. Qin gave her

266
00:09:12,010 --> 00:09:12,970
a cooked duck,

267
00:09:12,970 --> 00:09:14,250
but she still managed to lose it.

268
00:09:14,250 --> 00:09:15,660
Her reputation is too exaggerated.

269
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:16,800
From what you're saying,

270
00:09:16,800 --> 00:09:18,040
her doctorate and being

271
00:09:18,040 --> 00:09:19,800
CBBC's youngest deputy director

272
00:09:19,800 --> 00:09:21,150
aren't all that impressive.

273
00:09:21,400 --> 00:09:22,490
I'm just saying

274
00:09:22,490 --> 00:09:23,510
someone is backing her.

275
00:09:23,800 --> 00:09:25,880
I feel like Mr. Zhou
is quite protective of her.

276
00:09:25,880 --> 00:09:26,730
What do you think?

277
00:09:26,730 --> 00:09:28,110
Could it be...

278
00:09:28,880 --> 00:09:29,820
Do you remember?

279
00:09:30,210 --> 00:09:31,850
During the last dinner at Leisure House,

280
00:09:31,850 --> 00:09:33,410
Director Gan said Director Tang's beauty

281
00:09:33,410 --> 00:09:34,250
is a resource.

282
00:09:34,330 --> 00:09:35,170
Now, that comment

283
00:09:35,170 --> 00:09:36,150
seems to mean something.

284
00:09:36,280 --> 00:09:37,470
What does it mean?

285
00:09:38,330 --> 00:09:39,920
Why don't you help me analyze it?

286
00:09:39,920 --> 00:09:40,990
I'll learn from you.

287
00:09:41,680 --> 00:09:43,230
Director Tang, I'll get back to work.

288
00:09:48,490 --> 00:09:49,330
The hottest item

